The 4th article was confusing because it mentioned the cricket match being played at Lord's in a couple of the questions, but it was played at a different venue, so I marked those questions 'poor'
Yes, don't reject participants who try their hardest to do great work. The task is a bit subjective, so decisions might not agree with a machine's findings.
